Egypt plans to spend 100 billion
Egyptian pounds ($17.25 billion) on infrastructure projects,
Finance Minister Youssef Boutros-Ghali said.  This budget will only be partially funded by the
government, he told reporters in Cairo today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
